by the end of 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 Unemployment in Russia has increased to roughly 8%. But in Ireland, a European 
Union member, it is double that. 
</P>
<P>
 Meantime, the Russian budget deficit yawns -- but not as wide as in some other 
European countries. And even the battered Russian ruble is stabilizing. 
</P>
<P>
