<P>
 Probe Sought on Coffee Price Hikes: The New York State Consumer Protection 
Board has asked the Justice Department to investigate the recent retail hikes 
amid steep jumps in futures prices for coffee that will not reach consumers for 
months. The agency said in a statement that the increases in consumer prices 
are unwarranted because the currently surging price of raw coffee should be 
reflected later, not now. Prices for green, unroasted coffee beans soared to 
eight-year highs recently, topping $2 a pound, after frosts in Brazil's 
coffee-growing regions damaged vast amounts of next year's crop. 
