<P>
 AT&T Awarded Telecom License in Britain: The company said it has been awarded 
the license to offer telecommunications, giving it more freedom to fight back 
against the joined forces of British Telecom and MCI.However, the long-distance 
firm cautioned that it must still go through a 28-day public consultation 
process. That process could reveal important details regarding just how far the 
British government will go in assuring an even playing field. Even if AT&T gets 
full access to the British market, it will be handicapped by its need to use 
existing networks of competitors such as British Telecom. Executives say the 
British market is already crowded with players. 
