<HEADLINE>
<P>
NITTY-GRITTY: INSIDE & OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * If size and style permit, rotate curtains and drapes to prevent certain 
areas of fabric from becoming overexposed to sun rays. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cover leg ends of metal furniture with rubber tips to reduce scrapes and 
rust marks on patio or deck. Or coat the bottom of each leg with a heavy layer 
of silicone rubber compound. Let dry overnight before setting right side up. 
</P>
<P>
 * To keep dogs away from garbage cans, sprinkle full-strength ammonia over 
bags before placing them in trash containers. 
</P>
<P>
 * When tying up tomato plants, use pantyhose that have been cut lengthwise. 
The nylon gives as the plants grow and will prevent cuts into the vine. 
</P>
