WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CALABASAS; FAIR TO OFFER SUPPORT FOR DISABLED YOUTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free fair to connect young people with disabilities to area support services 
will be held Sunday at Soka University of America. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by Special Parents Advocacy, Training and Support group of Las 
Virgenes, the free fair will be held from 1 p.m. to 4 p.m. in the campus 
cafeteria, located at 26800 Mulholland Highway. 
</P>
<P>
 SPATS is a nonprofit group that offers support for young people up to 22 years 
old with physical, emotional or learning disabilities. 
</P>
<P>
 Gail Paplanus, SPATS coordinator, said the fair will present a "mishmash" of 
information on services from about 16 different agencies that serve the north 
San Fernando Valley and east Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 The afternoon event will also feature a guided nature walk, which will begin 
at 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 For further information, call Paplanus at (818) 340-4296. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
