WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; A REAL FOOTBALLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the "It's never too late to learn something new" category: Zacchary Bryan, 
12, of Glendale gave the Raiders' Nolan Harrison a lesson in juggling a soccer 
ball at a preview day of SoccerFest on Thursday at the Los Angeles Convention 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 In a ring in the center of the 500,000 square-foot soccer festival, Bryan 
showed that he was clearly more adept at juggling -- keeping a soccer ball in 
the air by kicking it -- than Harrison. 
</P>
<P>
 "As a football player, I thought I was quick-footed," Harrison said. "But I'm 
not as quick as these guys." 
</P>
<P>
 Final score: Bryan 15, Harrison 3. 
</P>
<P>
 SoccerFest continues through July 17. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
