WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; HIGHER CALLING? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Evenimentul Zilei 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The priest who tolled church bells to announce Romania's anti-communist 
revolution has moved on to sports.He now prays for a World Cup victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Valeria Iordanescu, wife of Romanian Coach Anghel Iordanescu, made a cash 
donation to the church of Father Sandi Mehedintu to pray for 40 days. 
</P>
<P>
 "God will be on Romania's side like in so many crucial moments in its 
history," she was quoted as saying in the daily Evenimentul Zilei in Bucharest. 
</P>
<P>
