DIGEST: BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First Baseman Chris Fick, who led Cal Lutheran in most offensive categories, 
has signed a free-agent contract with the St. Louis Cardinals and will report 
today to San Bernardino, an independent team in the Class-A California League. 
</P>
<P>
 Fick, 24, a graduate of Newbury Park High, was signed by his brother, Cardinal 
scout Chuck Fick. Chris Fick, a 6-foot-2, 185-pound, left-handed batter, hit 
.367 with 14 home runs and 52 runs batted in for the Kingsmen in the spring. 
</P>
<P>
 Geoff Zahn, a former major league pitcher, has been named an assistant at 
Pepperdine. 
</P>
<P>
 Zahn, who was an assistant at The Master's College in 1987 and 1988, will 
coach the pitchers under the Waves' new coach, Pat Harrison. Zahn was also 
athletic director at The Master's, where he hired Harrison to be the Mustangs' 
head coach in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 Zahn pitched in the majors from 1973-85, playing with the Dodgers, Chicago 
Cubs, Minnesota Twins and Angels. He had a career record of 111-109 and a 3.74 
ERA. Football  
</P>
<P>
 Troy Jackson, head coach at Bethel Christian High for the past three years, is 
expected to be hired as an assistant coach at Antelope Valley College, pending 
board approval later this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Jackson, who had an 11-19 record at Bethel Christian, guided the Eagles to the 
1993 Desert Mountain League title. They advanced to the second round of the 
Southern Section Division XI playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 A 1982 graduate of Canyon High, Jackson will coach the linebackers. Rugby  
</P>
<P>
 The Eagle Rock Sevens Rugby tournament will begin at 9 a.m. July 16 at the 
John Ferraro Athletic Fields in Griffith Park. The tournament, which includes 
rugby clubs from across Southern California, runs all day and admission is 
free. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-784-2963. Motor Sports  
</P>
<P>
 A preview of the M-Car Grand Prix, an amateur race of miniature cars, will be 
held at Saugus Speedway on Tuesday at 7 p.m. The race is a fund-raiser for the 
Santa Clarita Child and Family Development Center, which is looking for 
potential sponsors to race in the event in October. Soccer 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. World Cup team members Alexi Lalas and Cobi Jones will be the featured 
instructors for an inaugural youth soccer camp near Griffith Park, July 25-29. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 213:964-3696. Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 The Conejo Parks and Recreation department will play host to the Lancer 
basketball camp, July 25-29, for boys and girls grades 6-11 at Thousand Oaks 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-495-4674. 
