<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA RACEWAY; BARTELS RUNS AWAY WITH SECOND STREET STOCK VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bill Bartels of Los Angeles ran away with his second Street Stock 20-lap main 
event before a small crowd Friday night at Ventura Raceway. 
</P>
<P>
 Bartels, who started fourth, took the lead on the fifth lap from Westlake's Al 
Adam. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam had gotten the jump at the start on pole-sitter Curtis Dietzch of 
Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara's James Weston spent the evening chasing Bartels but could not 
come up with enough power to make a pass, and when the pair hit lapped traffic 
with two laps remaining, Bartels was able to put the slower cars between 
himself and Weston to guarantee the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Defending champion and current points leader Paul Moore finished third. 
</P>
<P>
 Bartels also won the first seven-lap heat, while Ventura's Jason Secor took 
the second Street Stock heat. 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo's Richard Webster went wire to wire in the 15-lap Mini Stock main 
after winning the second of two seven-lap heat races. Points leader Bruce 
Dunson of Ventura grabbed the first heat, and finished fourth in the Main. 
</P>
<P>
 Webster needed only one lap to take command in the heat race, after starting 
fourth in a five-car field. 
</P>
<P>
 The 15-lap Pony Stock Main Event featured five lead changes and an apparent 
dead-heat finish, as Oxnard's Trish Remley crossed the finish line in tandem 
with Don DeAzevedo. 
</P>
<P>
 DeAzevedo, who led five laps in the middle of the race as well as the final 
lap, was set back to fourth place for rough driving, giving Remley the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Verdun and Michael VanDeventer won the two seven-lap heat races. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Cole of Santa Maria added to his lead in the points standings with a 
victory in the 15-lap IMCA Modified feature. Bill Lauer, also of Santa Maria, 
won the eight-lap heat, with Cole finishing fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Howard of Ventura won the 15-lap IMCA Sprint feature by one-quarter lap 
over his teammate, Daryl Rogers of Palmdale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070994-0255 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 059090 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
