<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOVAK PACES WOODLAND HILLS WEST'S 8-4 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Novak went three for four with two doubles and two runs batted in, 
leading Woodland Hills West to an 8-4 victory over Encino Friday in an American 
Legion baseball District 20 Western Division game at El Camino Real High. 
</P>
<P>
 Novak was the leader of a 12-hit attack, but Justin Balser also had three 
hits, including a double.Billy Burnette added two hits and an RBI for Woodland 
Hills West (10-4), which pulled closer to Encino (12-2) in the Western Division 
race. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Kmet pitched a complete game for Woodland Hills West, striking out one 
and walking six. Three of those walks came in the bottom of the seventh inning, 
when Encino threatened by loading the bases with two out. But Jessie Slade 
flied out to end the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Encino managed only five hits. The biggest was Brad Farlow's two-run home run 
in the first inning.  
</P>
<P>
 Farlow's homer pulled Encino to within a run after Woodland Hills West had 
taken a 3-0 lead in the top of the first. 
</P>
<P>
 Encino tied the game with a run in the bottom of the second, but Woodland 
Hills West regained the lead with a run in the third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
